ğŸ¯ Objective:
Improve the visual hierarchy of this Vue + PrimeVue 4 application to enhance content readability and user focus.

ğŸ“Œ PrimeVue 4.x Styling Rules:
- DO NOT use legacy theme CSS imports â€” this app uses styled mode with:
  import Aura from '@primevue/themes/aura'
  app.use(PrimeVue, { theme: { preset: Aura } })

ğŸ› ï¸ Instructions:
- Use `<Card>` components to group related sections (e.g., metadata, AI suggestions, user input).
- Use `<Divider>` to clearly separate logical sections on the page.
- Use heading elements (`<h2>`, `<h3>`) or `<span class="text-xl font-bold">` to establish section titles.
- Use PrimeFlex classes (`p-mb-3`, `p-mt-2`, etc.) for spacing between elements.
- Add subtle icons using `pi pi-*` classes inside headings for visual emphasis.

ğŸ“¦ Required Components:
- `Card` (for logical grouping)
- `Divider` (for visual sectioning)
- `Text` elements with controlled `font-weight`, `font-size` via classes
- Optional: `Icon`, `Avatar`, `Tag` for extra context in headings

ğŸ“Œ Keep styling consistent with the Aura theme (styled mode). Avoid legacy CSS theme usage.

ğŸ’¡ Example:
```vue
<Card>
  <template #title>
    <span class="text-xl font-bold">
      <i class="pi pi-user mr-2"></i> Patient Details
    </span>
  </template>
  <template #content>
    <div class="p-mb-3">Name: John Doe</div>
    <div class="p-mb-3">Age: 45</div>
  </template>
</Card>

<Divider />

<Card>
  <template #title>AI Assessment</template>
  <template #content>
    <p>Confidence Score: 93%</p>
  </template>
</Card>
